 |          TITLE:                                                            |
 |CONSAT INIT PROBLEM                                                         |
 |          DESCRIPTION OF PROBLEM:                                           |
 |DURING SIO ASYNC CHANNEL INITIALIZATION SEVERAL SVCS ARE ISSUED IN          |
 |SEQUENCE AND THE SIO CHIP DOES NOT HAVE ADEQUATE TIME TO COMPLETE EACH      |
 |SVC BEFORE THE NEXT COME DOWN.  UNDER THIS CIRCUMSTANCE THE SIO PORT        |
 |TRANSMITTER IS DISABLED AND THE PORT IS EFFECTIVELY HUNG.  THIS PROBLEM     |
 |IS NOT NEW BUT HAS REQUIRED A DELAY PATCH FOR VERSION 6.04 AND 6.40.  FOR   |
 |A PICO ENGINE THE DELAY SHOULD BE IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD OF 20 MS WHILE AN     |
 |ENGINE NEEDS ABOUT 9 MS FOR THE INITIALIZATION SEQUENCE TO COMPLETE.        |
 |                                                                            |
